SpatiumDDI appliance state directory.

Files dropped here on first boot or by cloud-init user-data:

  .env             Generated by spatiumddi-firstboot on first power-on.
                   Holds POSTGRES_PASSWORD / SECRET_KEY /
                   CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPTION_KEY / DNS_AGENT_KEY /
                   DHCP_AGENT_KEY / SPATIUMDDI_VERSION /
                   CONTROL_PLANE_URL / BOOTSTRAP_PAIRING_CODE.
                   Sourced by the spatium-supervisor pod's
                   entrypoint at startup via the hostPath bind
                   mount at /etc/spatiumddi-host/.env.

  release          Optional. Set SPATIUMDDI_VERSION=<calver-tag> to
                   pin a specific release at first boot. cloud-init
                   can write this via:
                     write_files:
                       - path: /etc/spatiumddi/release
                         content: SPATIUMDDI_VERSION=2026.05.07-1

  role-config      Written by spatium-install on the installer
                   wizard's last step. Carries ROLE
                   (full-stack / frontend-core / application) +
                   CONTROL_PLANE_URL + BOOTSTRAP_PAIRING_CODE.

Issue #183 Phase 7 — the appliance is k3s-only; no docker. The
service stack is the spatiumddi-appliance Helm chart, applied via
the bootstrap manifest at /var/lib/rancher/k3s/server/manifests/
spatium-bootstrap.yaml that spatiumddi-firstboot renders on each
boot. k3s's helm-controller picks it up + brings the supervisor
pod online; subsequent role assignments come from the control
plane's heartbeat response → supervisor PATCHes the HelmChart CR.

Operator commands:
  spatiumddi-stack-status              k3s + pod inventory + version pin
  systemctl status spatiumddi-firstboot
  systemctl status k3s                 the cluster control plane
  kubectl get pods -A                  every workload, every namespace
  kubectl logs -n spatium <pod>        per-pod logs
  journalctl -u k3s -f                 cluster-level events
  tail -f /var/log/spatiumddi/firstboot.log    full orchestrator output
